    <chapter title="Basic Execution" id="basic-execution">
        
        <chapter title="Command Line" id="command-line">
            <p>Run games directly from the terminal:</p>
            
            <code-block lang="bash">
                # Navigate to project directory
                cd /path/to/16Games-in-Cpp
                
                # Run a compiled game
                ./tetris
                ./snake
                ./chess
            </code-block>
        </chapter>
        
        <chapter title="From Game Directory" id="from-directory">
            <p>Some games work better when run from their own directory:</p>
            
            <code-block lang="bash">
                # Navigate to game directory
                cd "01 Tetris"
                
                # Run the game
                ../tetris
                
                # Or compile and run in one step
                g++ -o tetris main.cpp -lsfml-graphics -lsfml-window -lsfml-system && ./tetris
            </code-block>
        </chapter>
        
    </chapter>

